      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A suit for $4,000 damages was\nfiled today by 2. F. Williams\nagainst the Great Northern Rail-\nway Co. Prior to August II plain\ntiff was freight brakeman run\nming between Wilson Creek and\nLeavenworth. AS they were pull\ning out of Wenatchee on the above\ndate, plaintiff attempted to board a\nfiat car on which the grab iron\"\nand \"stirrup\" were loose and fell.\nHe says he sustained numerous in\nternal injuries as a result of a\nbackward fall upon a large cinder."
    }
